@tibkiss we cover these tests with different tox profiles [[1]](https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/master/sdks/python/tox.ini#L61). In the pre-submit tests for the python-sdk we have three profiles of tests right now (beam without dependencies, beam with GCP, beam with cython).

The default tests do not enable GCP by default so that a user can work/develop on beam without having to depend on any Google Cloud specific dependencies. I agree that coverage on the default profile is not correctly representative of the state of the project but this is done so that if someone runs `python setup.py test` that should just work without throwing errors due to any particular runner specific dependencies.

[1] https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/master/sdks/python/tox.ini#L61

@sb2nov : Thanks for your response. I think it makes sense to keep the doc about args in there: 
I initially thought  that it is a copy-paste mistake (due to lack of direct constructor), but your explanation & parent constructor explains it all. 

Your idea on validation is great: It'll remove the ambiguity caused by inherited constructor and also increase safety. Will create a Ticket / PR for that soon.
